Technology Brief -- 3Com Corp.:
   U.K.'s BICC Group to Sell
   Data-Networking Business
Under the agreement, 3Com will purchase the BICC assets
for about $25 million in cash, plus a warrant for 500,000
shares of 3Com common stock. 3Com will take a one-time charge
of about $10 million in its fiscal third quarter related to
the transaction.
   In over-the counter trading yesterday afternoon, the
company's stock was quoted at $13.625, up 50 cents.
   The transaction is expected to be completed next month.